Template: oversip/overwrite-config
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Overwrite existing OverSIP configuration files?
 Configuration files for OverSIP already exist in /etc/oversip/.
 If you choose to overwrite them, your current configuration will be
 replaced with the package defaults. The old files will be backed up
 with a .dpkg-old extension.
 .
 If you choose not to overwrite them, the package defaults will be
 installed with a .dpkg-dist extension and you can manually merge
 changes.

Template: oversip/overwrite-tls
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Overwrite existing OverSIP TLS certificate files?
 TLS certificate and key files for OverSIP already exist in /etc/oversip/tls/.
 If you choose to overwrite them, your current TLS files will be
 replaced with the package defaults (demo certificates). The old files
 will be backed up with a .dpkg-old extension.
 .
 WARNING: Overwriting TLS files may break existing TLS connections.
 Only overwrite if you understand the consequences or are doing a
 fresh installation.